5. Code Changes and Check-in
Open the solution in Visual Studio and navigate to the first class in your Solution Explorer.
Make a simple change—such as adding a single comment line to the code—and save it.
Also, include a .gitignore file under your repository to ensure unnecessary files aren’t tracked.

Once these changes are made, you should see them listed in your Git Changes tab. Review the changes to confirm that they are correct, and once you're satisfied, proceed with Commit All.

