2.  Review Process

 The pull request will be reviewed by the designated team members or stakeholders. Reviewers will check the code, suggest changes, and approve the PR once everything looks good.

3. Address Feedback

 If feedback is provided, make necessary code changes and update the PR with the new commits. This process may continue until the pull request is approved.

4. Approval and Merge

 Once all feedback is addressed and the pull request is approved, merge the changes into the target branch. Depending on your setup, the merge may be automatic or require manual intervention.

5. Complete the PR

 After merging, mark the pull request as completed to finalize the process.

If necessary, delete the feature branch to keep the repository clean.



